			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If ROM was mapped to ZP, you wouldn't be able to use dynamic pointers, and constant pointers are completely pointless, since you could just as well use absolute addressing. The stack would also be ROM, making it completely useless (except for reading 256 bytes from ROM using PLA). The 6502 was designed to have RAM on the lower part of the address space, there's no way around that.<br /><br />PPU registers in ZP (as are the TIA registers in the Atari 2600) would be cool! We'd be able to transfer more data during vblank, and  raster effects would be slightly easier to time. The writes could even go through to RAM so you could &quot;read back&quot; values written to write-only registers.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

