					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">you can put your sprite buffer in ZP if you want.</div><br /><br />I've thought about putting the OAM buffer in the stack. It's not as ridiculous as it sounds, you just need to make sure your stack is nearly empty at the point you push the buffer to the OAM. You might have to shuffle a few bytes around before and after that, and limit your # of sprites to 56. But, it might potentially free up some extra RAM.<br /><br />Edit. But don't put the sprite buffer in the zero page. That would be dumb.</div>

					
