					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">To the contrary, <em>everything</em> should be DRAM.<br /><br />DRAM is cheaper (edit: cheaper=smaller per bit; in the 2C02 each bit of SRAM is 174% the area of each bit of DRAM), and in the NMOS technology that's used in the NES it's even lower power.<br /><br />Now, why did Nintendo have a buggy DRAM controller inside the PPU? That's a valid question. But not really different from any of the other &quot;why hardware bug&quot; questions.</div>

					
